    <title>Here is my list of PVP issues</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=10552</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I felt the need to post my list of PVP issues that are not being addressed:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; PVP Issues list that have been in "Discussion" since Aug '04.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; Ruleset that has no CLEAR defining line of "rights and wrongs".&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3.&amp;nbsp; Lack of enforcement of any stated rules (i.e. not enough GM presence on the server.)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4.&amp;nbsp; Lack of knowledge of the rules by the "Governing Body" (in conjunction with item 3.)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Those were the top 4 for me.&amp;nbsp; The merge just broke the camel's back.&amp;nbsp; What I feel is happening is I am being fed a bunch of stuff as a stalling or delaying tactic by the people who produce a broken product.&amp;nbsp; It's unfortunate, considering my 4.5 year tenure playing this game will officially&amp;nbsp; close as of May-June (subscription runs out.)&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I personally think I gave it all the benefit of the doubt.&amp;nbsp; Loose ruleset that left WAY too much room for interpretation, I continued to play.&amp;nbsp; Non-existant consistency within the GM staff on ruleings, I continued to play.&amp;nbsp;Loopholes (see interpretation) for the GM's to do nothing what so ever, I continued to play.&amp;nbsp; Complete disregard or changes at such a pace it makes a snail appear to move at light speed, I think 4.5 years is enough.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I believe it has been suggested somewhere that SOE started these changes so that they could finally let EQ die out and propagate EQ2 as their next cash cow is becoming a reality.&amp;nbsp; Granted, this is a personal opinion, but think on this: Why would they have to merge servers if the population was there?&amp;nbsp; Obviously the&amp;nbsp; population is going somewhere.&amp;nbsp; I know I have.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;With that, this is my final farewell to Rallos Zek (now just Zek), the home for me for the last 4.5 years.&amp;nbsp; I have moved on.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Deuronn Goodfellow&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
