&lt;DIV&gt;I would like to ask around about&amp;nbsp;a minor matter&amp;nbsp;: The possiblity of making the monk's Dragon Punch ability slighty easier to resist. I'm a chanter and&amp;nbsp;have 465mr (to be honest I'm actually not 100% sure it's even mr it checks against. If it's not then I'm sorry for my presumption)&amp;nbsp;and I still only seem to resist it like 1 out of 10 hits. Now as a caster, fighting a monk in high end game with 8k+hp unbuffed etc, well unless I have a corner to pin myself into to anull the effect of DP it's almost a certain loss. If&amp;nbsp;I'm fighting a monk in a&amp;nbsp;cornerless environment&amp;nbsp;it's damn near impossible to make my mana and hp last against his sick&amp;nbsp;melee dps and his DPs constantly knocking me back and interrupting my runes, nukes etc even with maxed&amp;nbsp;defensive aa's, decent mana preservation (30% on beneficials) etc. Maybe it's just me and a few others suffering from this. Sometimes I've been successful in&amp;nbsp;taking one step forward after being DP'd and then "regaining my concentration", but&amp;nbsp;my cpu is pretty&amp;nbsp;sucky and lags alot&amp;nbsp;in most&amp;nbsp;post-pop zones so that strategy is pretty impossible to rely on in any way.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Throw in a Ton-Po's Staff of Understanding and&amp;nbsp;as a pure caster - at least as a chanter -&amp;nbsp;you're going to either run or die if it's 1v1. Especially for me as a chanter fighting a monk I have to kill him with in 6 mins of him using his mend for the&amp;nbsp;1st time. So if I simply rely on rapture/nuking (with SOTI)&amp;nbsp;him to death a monk in high-end game will with like&amp;nbsp;85% certainty out-regen and&amp;nbsp;outresist my (pretty feeble) nukes even with maxed crit nukes and devastating (destructive? I forgot)&amp;nbsp;fury aa's. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So basically I have to rely on him killing himself on my DS (27 selfbuffed, with 9th(!)&amp;nbsp;coldain ring,&amp;nbsp;feedback and AHR neck), my pet (if he doesn't opt for killing it) proc'ing&amp;nbsp;DD's on him and the occational rune while I emphatically re-rune myself. Atm the DP is what makes the difference. After epic and&amp;nbsp;aa rune is clicked it's very likely that a monk can deny me the chance&amp;nbsp;to channel my 2.5 sec cast time rune&amp;nbsp;untill I'm dead, through using his DP.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hope I'm not offending&amp;nbsp;anyone, and I'm aware that it is a small matter. Just wondering if anyone else agrees with this.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
